00 for trade in the Indian Ocean region. At its height, the British East India Company had a private army which was twice the size of the British Army, ruled large sections of India, and revenues in the millions.","url":"https://www.historic-uk.com/HistoryUK/HistoryofEngland/The-East-India-Company/","urlTitle":"Historic UK - The East India Company","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705212,"age":116,"year":"1620","julianDay":2312753,"title":"The Pilgrims Board the Mayflower","description":"\"The Pilgrims boarded the Mayflower in search of religious freedom in the New World in September 1620. The Mayflower set sail from Plymouth, England, with 102 passengers, 40 of whom called themselves \"\"Saints.\"\" After two stormy months at sea, the ship reached the New World. Nearly half of the group died during their first winter due to malnutrition and the harsh New England winter.\"","url":"https://www.themayflowersociety.org/the-pilgrims/pilgrim-history","urlTitle":"The Mayflower Society - Pilgrim History","jurisdictionLevel":0}],"lifeSummary":"Giles Hills was born in 1504, in England. He married Mrs Giles Hills in 1524, in Bedfordshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 1 daughter."},"et":{"1504–":"1504–Surnud","1506–Female":"1506–Surnud","1525–1570":"1525–1570","1530–Female":"1530–Surnud","1504–Male":"1504–Surnud","1571":"1571","1570":"1570","1525":"1525","1569":"1569","1558":"1558","       1524":"1524","1600":"1600","1620":"1620","1530":"1530","about 1530":"umbes 1530","1506":"1506","1549":"1549","1504":"1504","Lyme Regis, Dorset, England":"Lyme Regis, Dorset, England","England":"England",",,Bedford, England":"Bedfordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1504–":"1504–Kuollut","1506–Female":"1506–Kuollut","1525–1570":"1525–1570","1530–Female":"1530–Kuollut","1504–Male":"1504–Kuollut","1571":"1571","1570":"1570","1525":"1525","1569":"1569","1558":"1558","       1524":"1524","1600":"1600","1620":"1620","1530":"1530","about 1530":"noin 1530